{"title_page": "Mali\u0161evo", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the Table at Infobox settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n| name                    = Malishev\u00eb\n| native_name             = {{unbulleted list |item_style=font-size:81%; | \u041c\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0448\u0435\u0432\u043e / {{native name|sr|Malishev\u00eb}}<br>''Malisheva'' or {{native name|sq|Malishev\u00eb}} }}\n| native_name_lang        = sr\n| other_name              = \n| settlement_type         = [[List of cities in Kosovo|Town]] and [[Municipalities of Kosovo|municipality]]\n| official_name           = \n<!-- images and maps  ----------->\n|image_skyline          =\n|imagesize              =\n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             =\n|seal_size              =\n|image_shield           =\n|shield_size            =\n|image_blank_emblem     = Stema e Komun\u00ebs Malishev\u00eb.svg\n|blank_emblem_type      = Emblem\n|blank_emblem_size      =\n|image_map              = File:Malishev\u00eb - Mali\u015fova.png\n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = Location of the municipality of Malishev\u00eb within Kosovo\n|pushpin_map            = \n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n<!-- Location ------------------>\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Kosovo]]{{efn|name=status}}\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Districts of Kosovo|District]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[District of Prizren]]\n|subdivision_type2      = \n|subdivision_name2      =\n<!-- Politics ----------------->\n| government_footnotes   =\n| government_type        =\n| leader_title           = Mayor\n| leader_party           = \n| leader_name            = Reqip Begaj\n| established_title      = \n| established_date       = \n<!-- Area    --------------------->\n| area_magnitude          = \n| unit_pref               = \n| area_blank1_title       = Urban\n| area_blank1_km2         = \n| area_blank2_title       = Municipal\n| area_blank2_km2         = 306\n| area_footnotes          = \n<!-- Population   ----------------------->\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_footnotes    =\n| population_note         =\n| population_blank1_title = Urban\n| population_blank1       = 3395\n| population_density_blank1_km2 = auto\n| population_blank2_title = Municipal\n| population_blank2       = 54613\n| population_density_blank2_km2 = auto\n<!-- General information  --------------->\n|timezone               = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n|utc_offset             = +1\n|timezone_DST           = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n|utc_offset_DST         = +2\n|coordinates            = {{coord|42|28|58|N|20|44|45|E|region:RS-KM|display=inline}}\n|elevation_footnotes    = <!--for references: use <ref> tags-->\n|elevation_m            = 538\n|elevation_ft           =\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n|postal_code_type       = Postal code\n|postal_code            = 24000\n|area_code              = +381\n|blank_name             = [[Vehicle registration plates of Kosovo|Car plates]]\n|blank_info             = 04\n|blank1_name            =\n|blank1_info            =\n|website                = {{url|http://kk.rks-gov.net/malisheve}}\n|footnotes              =\n}}\n{{confused|Malishev\u00eb, Gjilan}}\n'''Malishev\u00eb''' ([[Serbian Cyrillic alphabet|Serbian Cyrillic]]: \u041c\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0448\u0435\u0432\u043e) or '''Malisheva''' ({{lang-sq|Malishev\u00eb}}), is a [[List of cities in Kosovo|town]] and [[Municipalities of Kosovo|municipality]] located in the [[District of Prizren|Prizren District]] of [[Kosovo]]{{efn|name=status}}. According to the 2011 census, the town of Malishev\u00eb has 3,395 inhabitants, while the municipality has 54,613 inhabitants.\n\n== History ==\nThe population of the town has historically been predominantly [[ethnic Albanian]]. The town was largely destroyed by Serbian forces in 1998.  Town residents only returned following the 1998 withdrawal of Serbian paramilitary police and military, in response to international pressures.<ref>[[Julius Strauss]], \"Albanian refugees nervously return to their Kosovo homes as Serbian troops pull out\".  ''[[Daily Telegraph]]'' via the ''[[National Post]]'', October 28, 1998, p. A12.</ref>  \n\nThe town became a stronghold for the ethnically Albanian [[Kosovo Liberation Army]] during the [[Kosovo War]] in 1999. The [[United Nations Interim Administration Mission in Kosovo]] (UNMIK) formally re-established the municipality of Malishev\u00eb in July 2000. During the war, a number of atrocities were committed by both Albanian and Yugoslav forces. One such incident occurred in Malishev\u00eb, the execution of no fewer than seven Serbian men, named the ''Malishev\u00eb Massacre''. The [[United Nations|UN]]-run Office on Missing Persons and Forensics began the excavations at the site in May 2005.\n\n==Economy==\nThere is one gold mine operating on the territory of Malishev\u00eb - [[Trpeza mine|Trpeza]].\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Historical populations\n|title=Municipal historical population\n| percentages = pagr\n|2011|54613 |2016<br>{{small|est.}}|57301\n|source = [http://pop-stat.mashke.org/kosovo-division.htm Division of Kosovo]\n}}\nAccording to the last official census done in 2011, the city of Malishev\u00eb has a population of 54,613 inhabitants. The municipality has ethnic [[Kosovo Albanians]] majority (54,501; 99.8%). Based on the population estimates from the Kosovo Agency of Statistics in 2016, the municipality has 58,282 inhabitants.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Subdivisions of Kosovo]]\n\n== Notes and references ==\n\n'''Notes:'''\n\n{{notes\n| notes =\n\n{{efn\n| name = status\n| {{Kosovo-note}}\n}}\n\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://kk.rks-gov.net/malisheve Municipality of Malisheve]\n* [http://www.osce.org/item/1210.html?html=1 OSCE Profile of Malishev\u00eb/Mali\u0161evo]<sup>(Dead link)</sup>\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060526083521/http://english.aljazeera.net/NR/exeres/15FC893C-D83C-426B-B599-D8A673DDD215.htm \"Serb mass grave found in Kosovo\" 15 May 2005]<sup>(Dead link)</sup>\n* [http://kosovareport.blogspot.com/2005/05/kosovo-government-backs-probe-into.html \"Kosovo government backs probe into Malisevo mass grave\" 17 May 2005]\n\n{{Kosovo municipalities}}\n\n{{coord|42|28|58|N|20|44|45|E|display=title|type:city_source:dewiki}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Malishev\u00eb}}\n[[Category:Populated places in Kosovo]]\n[[Category:Municipalities of Kosovo]]\n[[Category:Cities in Kosovo]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the Table at Infobox settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n| name                    = Mali\u0161evo\n| native_name             = {{unbulleted list |item_style=font-size:81%; | \u041c\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0448\u0435\u0432\u043e / {{native name|sr|Mali\u0161evo}}<br>''Malisheva'' or {{native name|sq|Malishev\u00eb}} }}\n| native_name_lang        = sr\n| other_name              = \n| settlement_type         = [[List of cities in Kosovo|Town]] and [[Municipalities of Kosovo|municipality]]\n| official_name           = \n<!-- images and maps  ----------->\n|image_skyline          =\n|imagesize              =\n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             =\n|seal_size              =\n|image_shield           =\n|shield_size            =\n|image_blank_emblem     = Stema e Komun\u00ebs Malishev\u00eb.svg\n|blank_emblem_type      = Emblem\n|blank_emblem_size      =\n|image_map              = File:Malishev\u00eb - Mali\u015fova.png\n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = Location of the municipality of Mali\u0161evo within Kosovo\n|pushpin_map            = \n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n<!-- Location -----